Nikita Borisov <nborisov@calum.csclub.uwaterloo.ca> writes:

> Attempt #1:
> compctl -g '*(-/x)' cd

Why don't you use `*(D-/x)' pattern?  The `d' means to include all the
dots except `.' and `..'.  I use:

compctl -g *(D-/) cd

in my .zshrc.

